<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3347&amp;p=24533#p24533"><![CDATA[
Just out of curiosity I tried applying a delta-codec to the smb_orig pattern data and got a file that was 11956 bytes (that is, about 18% of the original file. or 73% if compared to a plain 2-bit represenation). It'd be interesting to try to implement the decoder in 6502 assembly sometime, since it's not very complex iirc (no multiplication/division needed).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1181">mic_</a> — Wed May 30, 2007 1:19 am</p><hr />
